in August 2003.  Objective of the EAP is to ensure the safety of all employees of McCain Foods, as established in compliance with 29 CFR 1910.38 of the OSHA General Industry Standards.  McCain Foods has received input from and worked with the Fort Atkinson Fire Department, Jefferson County Local Emergency Planning Committees (LEPC) and State of Wisconsin HAZMAT organizations to ensure compliance in the emergency response areas.  

PLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY

McCain Foods conducts a monthly meeting to review ammonia system, document unsafe conditions, and discuss improvements to equipment.  A $30,000 budget is set aside for review of the system and any necessary improvements.  In addition, valves are checked annually and equipment is calibrated every six months, both are conducted by an outside agency.
